  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Corruption\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Preventive Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset freezing and seizure\n- Criminal prosecution of money laundering offenses\n\n4. Global Compliance Mechanisms:\n- International cooperation between law enforcement\n- Information sharing between financial institutions\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n\n5. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Potential imprisonment\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
